The paper deals with the problem of determining the Generalized Degrees of Freedom (GDoF) region achievable by treating interference as noise (TIN) with proper power control for single-antenna Gaussian interference channels. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT), networked systems (cs.NI), game theory (cs.GT), and combinatorial optimization (cs.DS). The paper also provides conditions for GDoF optimality for a new class of interference networks, which falls under the category of social networks (cs.SI).
